ame of the source / type used in the transformation process.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="138" lineend="141" name="getSource" returns="string" signature="string getSource()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the source as a path instead of a regular value.&#10;&#10;This method applies the following rules to the value of $source:&#10;&#10;1. if the template_path parameter is set and that combined with the&#10;   source gives an existing file; return that.&#10;2. if the value exists as a file (either relative to the current working&#10;   directory or absolute), do a realpath and return it.&#10;3. Otherwise prepend it with the phpDocumentor data folder, if that does&#10;   not exist: throw an exception&#10;&#10;@throws Exception if no valid file could be found.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="159" lineend="202" name="getSourceAsPath" returns="string" signature="string getSourceAsPath()"><variable line="195" name="file" /><variable citdl="rtrim()" line="164" name="path" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Filename of the resulting artifact relative to the root.&#10;&#10;If the query results in a set of artifacts (multiple nodes / array);&#10;then this string must contain an identifying variable as returned by the&#10;writer.&#10;&#10;@param string $artifact Name of artifact to generate; usually a filepath.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="215" lineend="218" name="setArtifact" signature="void setArtifact(string $artifact)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="215" name="artifact" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the name of the artifact.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="225" lineend="228" name="getArtifact" returns="string" signature="string getArtifact()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets an array of parameters (key =&gt; value).&#10;&#10;@param string[] $parameters Associative multidimensional array containing&#10;    parameters for the Writer.&#10;&#10;@return void" il